data.title: Sir Edward "1st Earl of Somerset" "2nd Duke of Somerset" (Sir Edward "1st Earl of Somerset" "2nd Duke of Somerset") Seymour (1506
data.meta_description: Sir Edward "1st Earl of Somerset" "2nd Duke of Somerset" Seymour was born on May 22, 1506 in Wolf Hall, Burbage, Wiltshire, England, son of Sir John IV Seymour of Wolf Hall of Somerset, KB; 1st Earl Bedford; Warden of Savernake; High Sheriff of Wiltshire and Margery Wentworth. He was married in the year 1516 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married in the year 1516 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married on March  9, 1524 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married on March  9, 1524 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married in the year 1527 in Savernake, Wiltshire, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married in the year 1527 in Savernake, Wiltshire, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married on March  9, 1532 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married on March  9, 1533 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married in the year 1537 in Somerset, England to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope He was married in the year 1552 in Somerset, England, UK to Lady Anne Duchess of Somerset Stanhope, they had 7 children., they gave birth to 1 child. He died on January 22, 1551 in Beheaded for treason,Tower Hill, London, England (burial in the Chapel of St Peter-ad-Vicula). This information is part of Genealogy Thrutchley/Anderson/Fitzgerel/Cox/Staley by Duane Thrutchley on Genealogy Online.
